io.spine.model.assemble

Class SpineAnnotationProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.annotation.processing.AbstractProcessor
      • io.spine.model.assemble.SpineAnnotationProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javax.annotation.processing.Processor
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AssignLookup

    @SPI
public abstract class SpineAnnotationProcessor
extends javax.annotation.processing.AbstractProcessor
    An abstract base for the Spine annotation processors.

    This class provides the handy lifecycle for the processors basing on their round-oriented nature.

    Be sure to add the fully qualified name of your implementation of this class to resources/META_INF/services/javax.annotation.processing.Processor to make it visible to the compiler.

    Warning: do not use standard Java throwables in the methods of this class to intentionally break the compilation. It may cause unreadable error messages. Use error() method instead with the error message. Use throwables only to state the programming mistakes in the processor itself.

    • Method Detail

      • getAnnotationType

        protected abstract java.lang.Class<? extends java.lang.annotation.Annotation> getAnnotationType()
        Retrieves the supported by this processor annotation type.

        Basic implementation example is: 

             @Override
     protected Class getAnnotationType() {
         return Assign.class;
     }

        Note: it's required that this method returns the same value on any invocation.

        Returns:
        the Class of the target annotation

      • processElement

        protected abstract void processElement(javax.lang.model.element.Element element)
        Performs the processing of the given annotated code element.

        It's guaranteed that the argument is annotated with the processor target annotation.

        The processing may include validation, code generation, etc.

      • getOption

        protected final com.google.common.base.Optional<java.lang.String> getOption(java.lang.String optName)
        Retrieves the value of the given annotation processor option.

        The options are passed to the compiler as follows: javac -Akey=value [...].

        Parameters:
        optName - the name of the desired option
        Returns:
        the value of the desired option or Optional.absent() if the option is not present in the processor or has no value (i.e. is a flag option)
